== Balance Change Log ==
{{PatchTableStart}}<onlyinclude>
{{PatchTableElement|2025-12-09|
{{DevComment|Hazard’s primary fire oriented powers weren’t keeping pace so Bonerot and Twin Fang are getting some extra bite to help him feel more threatening when he commits. On the other hand, Ability Power oriented builds were doing a little too much while being easy and cheap to build.}}

{{al|Bonerot}} - Power
* Damage increased to 20 (Up from 10).

{{al|Twin Fang}} - Power
* Damage increased to 75% (Up from 65%).

{{al|Touch-Up's Touch Up}} - Epic Ability Hero Item
* Ability Power decreased to 5% (Down from 10%).
* Spike Guard damage decreased to 20% (Down from 25%).
* Duration decreased to 3s (Down from 5s).
* Cost increased to 12000 (Up from 10000).

{{al|Phreak Foil}} - Epic Survival Hero Item
* Cost increased to 12000 (Up from 10000).
}}
{{PatchTableElement|2025-11-11|
{{DevComment|Hazard’s wall-focused powers were hitting a little too hard, dishing out big burst damage on top of strong zoning potential. We’ve reduced the knockback damage for both Off The Wall and Fortress to make the ability feel fairer to play against while keeping its area control and impact intact.}}

{{al|Off The Wall}} - Power
* Damage decreased to 60 (Down from 80).

{{al|Fortress}} - Power
* Damage decreased to 25 (Down from 40).
}}
